<p>A cold snap bringing snow, ice and sub-zero temperatures has caused deadly accidents and widespread disruption across parts of Europe this week, with at least six deaths reported in France and Bosnia. Major transport hubs and commuter networks have been hit, leaving many passengers stranded and prompting extensive flight, train and road cancellations in several countries. Forecasters and airport operators warned that further snow could keep delays rolling into Wednesday in places including Amsterdam and Brussels, extending the knock-on effects for travelers.</p><img src='https://kagiproxy.com/img/maclRgcSHGupNSID7MyDWHjIdZNAbQ83_brpPZwEpLVEbJHMgfqeLnuDmSHQIKoawFrhcL3rgR8ZKLTmGApdVZ3WsdMpKmhi3XCzuMu1tSgdv91SJnJqsfCyBlnaPBEu9jkkQWZp3sSdoRh1uDYBXHAlvjMRN6OA-qb99we2iINnrOz9zKcCki9ua16IP6t3oZtv4r7C' alt='Travelers at Amsterdam Airport Schiphol check updates amid delays and cancellations.' /><br /><h3>Highlights:</h3><ul><li>Airport operations: Amsterdamâ€™s Schiphol airport reported more than 800 flight cancellations, while Paris airports grounded another 140 flights as snow intensified operational constraints.</li><li>Balkans impacts: In parts of the Balkans, heavy snow and rain were reported to have triggered flooding and power outages alongside the wintry conditions.</li><li>Northwest closures: Road closures and rail disruption were reported across northwestern Europe, including Britain, France and the Netherlands, as ice made travel unsafe.</li><li>Passenger experience: With departure boards packed with delays, travelers at Schiphol crowded around updates as airlines worked through rebooking and cancellations.</li></ul><h3>Perspectives:</h3><ul><li>Airport and transport operators: They prioritized safety and de-icing limits, cancelling large numbers of flights and warning of continued disruption as conditions worsened. (<a href='https://www.france24.com/en/europe/20260107-europe-braces-for-further-travel-chaos-as-deadly-cold-snap-brings-more-snow'>France 24</a>)</